fntsample
------------------------------------------
fntsample is a tool that can be used to make font samples that show coverage of
the font and are similar in appearance to Unicode Charts. It was developed for
use with DejaVu Fonts project.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.2.0-1
  libcairo2-1.17.4-1
  libfontconfig1-2.13.1-2
  libfreetype6-2.10.4-2
  libglib2.0_0-2.54.3-1
  libintl8-0.21-1
  libpango1.0_0-1.40.14-1
  perl_base-5.32.1-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.37-1
  cmake-3.20.0-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-11.2.0-1
  libcairo-devel-1.17.4-1
  libfontconfig-devel-2.13.1-2
  libfreetype-devel-2.10.4-2
  libglib2.0-devel-2.54.3-1
  libintl-devel-0.21-1
  libpango1.0-devel-1.40.14-1
  ninja-1.10.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/eugmes/fntsample

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/eugmes/fntsample/archive/release/5.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack fntsample-5.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./fntsample-5.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/fntsample-5.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/fntsample-5.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(fntsample)
  /usr/bin/fntsample.exe
  /usr/bin/pdf-extract-outline
  /usr/bin/pdfoutline
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/fntsample.README
  /usr/share/doc/fntsample/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/fntsample/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/fntsample/README.rst
  /usr/share/locale/uk/LC_MESSAGES/fntsample.mo
  /usr/share/man/man1/fntsample.1.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/pdf-extract-outline.1.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/pdfoutline.1.gz

